  "title": "Error: requiring unknown module \"undefined\" when app does not have internet",
  "body": "<!--\r\n  Thanks for participating in this project! We will try to answer as soon as possible 🙏\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug 🐛**\r\nWhen the app is disconnected from any network, trying to import anything from `react-instantsearch/connectors` results in the app crashing with the following error message: \r\n\r\n**To Reproduce 🔍**\r\n\r\n1. Import anything from `react-instantsearch/connectors`\r\n2. Disconnect device from internet\r\n3. Crash \r\n\r\n**Expected behavior 💭**\r\nThe app not to crash when using algolia's functions without internet\r\n\r\n**Environment:**\r\n - OS: [e.g. iOS / mac / android]\r\n - Version 4.4.1\r\n\r\nScreenshot: http://prntscr.com/jj9arb",
